HEADWORD: Case system
<hw>Case system</hw>. <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The system of teaching law in which the instruction is primarily a historical and inductive study of leading or selected cases, with or without the use of textbooks for reference and collateral reading.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caseum</ent>⟦br⟧
